-- Beijing Government Asks for `Baseline' Wage Increase of 11% for Workers
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-08T01:06:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/beijing-government-asks-for-baseline-wage-increase-of-11-for-workers.html

          
          
             The Beijing government has asked
companies to raise “baseline” wages by 11 percent, according
to 2010 salary guidelines published yesterday.  
 The guidelines recommend raises for workers of between 3
percent and 16 percent this year.  
